UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Terrance JACKSON, Defendant-Appellant. No. 10-30144

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 8, 2010. Spiro G. Latsis, Assistant U.S. Attorney, Diane Hollenshead Copes, Esq., Assistant U.S. Attorney, Stephen Andrew Higginson, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, New Orleans, LA, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Robin Elise Schulberg, Assistant Federal Public Defender, Federal Public Defender’s Office, New Orleans, LA, Cynthia M. Cimino, Federal Public Defender’s Office, New Orleans, LA, for Defendant-Appellant. Before KING, BENAVIDES, and PRADO, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Terrance Jackson has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Jackson has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
